19:14.321 --> 19:15.322
Nothing.

19:18.158 --> 19:20.577
Can I contact
the people you told?

19:21.286 --> 19:23.413
You told me this was private.

19:24.665 --> 19:28.168
He'll have spies watching you now,
as we speak.

19:28.710 --> 19:30.295
I hope you know that.

19:44.268 --> 19:47.187
[sighs]

19:52.067 --> 19:53.652
-[cell phone buzzing]
-[baby cooing]

19:53.735 --> 19:55.404
Shh, shh, shh…

19:56.655 --> 19:58.073
[whispers] Hello?

19:58.156 --> 20:00.033
Hey, Megan, this is Jodi Kantor.

20:00.117 --> 20:01.201
Is this a bad time?

20:01.827 --> 20:04.663
Uh… Um, no. It's fine.

20:04.746 --> 20:06.957
-[baby cooing]
-Oh, I hear her.

20:07.666 --> 20:08.876
How's it all going?

20:09.626 --> 20:11.670
[Megan] Yeah, it's, um…

20:11.753 --> 20:13.630
I just got her down.

20:15.924 --> 20:17.759
It's the toughest part, I think.

20:18.427 --> 20:19.761
Is it?

20:19.845 --> 20:21.388
I found it to be so.

20:22.097 --> 20:25.475
With my first daughter,
I had postpartum depression.

20:27.686 --> 20:30.772
Everyone's so excited, and it's like…

20:32.274 --> 20:33.525
you're just not there.

20:35.235 --> 20:36.236
Right.

20:39.031 --> 20:40.616
So, I got your email.

20:41.408 --> 20:42.492
How's it all going?

20:42.576 --> 20:44.536
Yeah… [chuckles]

20:45.162 --> 20:48.498
I feel like there are
a lot of women who have…

20:49.958 --> 20:52.336
been through something with him.

20:53.629 --> 20:56.590
But they find it hard to talk.

20:57.216 --> 21:00.552
And those who do talk to me
don't want to go on the record.

21:01.553 --> 21:02.971
In your previous stories,

21:04.139 --> 21:07.434
how did you persuade women
to tell you what had happened to them?

21:09.478 --> 21:10.938
Yeah, so…

21:12.314 --> 21:13.774
It's difficult.

21:13.857 --> 21:15.275
They're terrified.

21:16.235 --> 21:17.569
A case I made was,

21:18.570 --> 21:22.199
"You know, I can't change
what happened to you in the past,

21:22.908 --> 21:26.411
but together, we may be able
to use your experience

21:26.495 --> 21:28.205
to help protect other people."

21:29.623 --> 21:31.542
The truth, basically.

21:32.376 --> 21:33.377
But yeah.

21:33.877 --> 21:37.798
It's hard to ask women to talk.

21:39.174 --> 21:41.051
[chattering]

21:55.399 --> 22:00.028
[Ashley] Then he asked me
to meet him, uh, really early.

22:00.112 --> 22:03.031
And I had been up all night filming,
and I was tired.

22:03.782 --> 22:07.536
I went over to The Peninsula hotel,
and at reception, I asked,

22:07.619 --> 22:10.706
"Is Mr. Weinstein in The Belvedere
restaurant or is he on the patio?"

22:10.789 --> 22:13.959
And they said, "Go to his room."

22:15.460 --> 22:20.007
And I went upstairs,
and Harvey was in his bathrobe.

22:21.091 --> 22:23.635
And he asked
if he could give me a massage.

22:24.428 --> 22:26.430
"No," I said.

22:27.556 --> 22:31.602
And then, um, he asked me to help him
pick out his clothes for the day.

22:32.519 --> 22:35.939
He, you know, started asking
for all these things,

22:36.023 --> 22:39.026
increasingly more sexual,
getting closer and closer.

22:39.109 --> 22:42.154
And I just said no
so many different times,

22:42.237 --> 22:44.072
and in so many different ways.

22:45.115 --> 22:49.411
And then he finally, um,
asked me to watch him take a shower.

22:50.287 --> 22:52.456
And I said, "Harvey,

22:52.539 --> 22:55.959
when I win an Academy Award
in a Miramax movie,

22:57.169 --> 22:58.962
I will give you a blow job."

22:59.046 --> 23:00.923
And I got out of there fast.

23:01.590 --> 23:02.925
What did you do?

23:03.008 --> 23:05.636
I told my dad,
I told my agent,

23:05.719 --> 23:08.305
I told the people
with whom I was filming that night,

23:08.388 --> 23:09.973
and Harvey punished me.

23:10.057 --> 23:12.309
I mean, he blackballed my career

23:12.392 --> 23:14.561
because I had the wherewithal
to refuse him.

23:14.645 --> 23:16.230
How do you know that?

23:16.313 --> 23:19.525
I would be standing with other actresses,
and he would blank me.

23:19.608 --> 23:23.028
There were roles for which I was up
that I mysteriously did not get,

23:23.111 --> 23:25.531
and I know today
that it was Harvey making a phone call.

23:25.614 --> 23:29.785
You know, I did an article about it,
and nobody did anything.

23:29.868 --> 23:32.913
You didn't identify him,
but did industry people know

23:32.996 --> 23:34.748
who you were talking about
in your article?

23:34.831 --> 23:36.250
Absolutely.

23:36.333 --> 23:38.961
And the abuse came raining down
on me, not on him.

23:39.545 --> 23:42.297
You know at the Women's March
when I did the "Nasty Woman" poem?

23:42.381 --> 23:44.591
I lost a huge advertising gig

23:44.675 --> 23:48.512
because a small group of people complained
that I was quoting the president.

23:48.595 --> 23:50.973
He used that language
and got elected.

23:51.056 --> 23:53.934
I quoted him, and I got fired.

23:54.017 --> 23:57.020
It is decades later,
and it's still the same sexism.

23:57.104 --> 24:00.607
And, Jodi, I would make the same choices
all over again,

24:00.691 --> 24:02.317
but I also would like to work.

24:06.363 --> 24:08.824
[Jodi] Lisa Bloom, the lawyer,
she wrote to me.

24:08.907 --> 24:10.534
-Gloria Allred's daughter?
-Yeah.

24:10.617 --> 24:13.912
-Do you know her?
-No, but I assume she wants to help.

24:13.996 --> 24:15.539
I forwarded the email to Emily.

24:15.622 --> 24:17.583
[chattering]

24:22.921 --> 24:24.756
Jodi? Lisa Bloom.

24:25.591 --> 24:26.925
"Big announcement,

24:27.009 --> 24:31.597
my book Suspicion Nation is being produced
by Harvey Weinstein and Jay-Z."

24:31.680 --> 24:33.307
Weinstein is producing her book?

24:34.391 --> 24:39.313
Lisa Bloom, daughter of feminist icon,
is working with Harvey Weinstein.

24:39.396 --> 24:41.064
But why would she do that?

24:41.148 --> 24:43.233
How much do you get paid for a miniseries?

24:43.317 --> 24:45.986
He's got to be behind
Lisa reaching out to you.

24:46.069 --> 24:48.322
So Weinstein knows
what we're doing.

24:56.580 --> 24:57.581
Sorry.

25:01.376 --> 25:03.462
[Matt] Do you wanna keep going
with Trump?

25:04.338 --> 25:07.132
[Rebecca] Or you could join Jodi
and look into Harvey Weinstein?

25:07.216 --> 25:09.009
[chuckles]

25:10.552 --> 25:12.971
I worry about whether
it makes a difference.

25:14.097 --> 25:17.518
These women spoke out against Trump,
and he still became president.

25:17.601 --> 25:20.145
But in the wake of O'Reilly,
there's possibility.

25:20.229 --> 25:21.396
[cell phone buzzing]

25:21.480 --> 25:22.481
Sorry.

25:23.106 --> 25:25.526
Craig. I've been trying to reach you.

25:26.777 --> 25:27.986
You've gotta show up.

25:29.530 --> 25:30.531
How's your daughter?

25:30.614 --> 25:32.115
[chuckles] She's great.

25:34.451 --> 25:35.786
Oh, s-- Um…

25:37.037 --> 25:38.580
Sorry. I, um--

25:38.664 --> 25:40.916
Thank you for the gift you--

25:41.458 --> 25:42.584
Um…

25:43.293 --> 25:44.795
Is anything bothering you?

25:45.504 --> 25:47.714
Besides no sleep
and diapers everywhere.

25:49.883 --> 25:50.968
Are you okay?

25:53.971 --> 25:55.430
I've found it quite…

25:56.849 --> 25:57.850
difficult.

25:59.309 --> 26:00.310
I'm sorry.

26:01.645 --> 26:02.771
Will working help?

26:03.355 --> 26:04.648
Yeah. Yeah.

26:05.524 --> 26:07.776
Absolutely. It's better now.

26:17.452 --> 26:19.121
-[journalist] Megan.
-Hey.

26:33.844 --> 26:35.637
[Megan] Are they all famous?

26:36.805 --> 26:38.515
[Jodi] Most of them, yes.

26:39.474 --> 26:43.687
I guess my question is just, like,
is this the best use of our time?

26:43.770 --> 26:47.691
Like, as opposed to other people
we could potentially be covering.

26:48.400 --> 26:51.987
People who can't speak out.
Actresses already have a voice.

26:52.070 --> 26:55.490
But they could also fear being punished
by the film industry for using it.

26:56.158 --> 26:57.242
Sure…

26:58.035 --> 27:01.955
but what is it exactly
that we're looking at here?

27:02.039 --> 27:04.750
We're looking at extreme
sexual harassment in the workplace.

27:06.293 --> 27:08.921
These young women walked into what
they all had reason to believe

27:09.004 --> 27:12.174
were "business meetings"
with a producer, an employer.

27:12.257 --> 27:13.467
They were hopeful.

27:13.550 --> 27:17.179
They were expecting a serious conversation
about their work or a possible project.

27:17.262 --> 27:20.682
Instead, they say he met them
with threats and sexual demands.

27:21.266 --> 27:23.060
They claim assault and rape.

27:23.977 --> 27:28.023
If that can happen to Hollywood actresses,
who else is it happening to?

27:29.441 --> 27:31.527
Do you think his employees
were targeted too?

27:32.110 --> 27:33.111
I do.

27:36.490 --> 27:40.744
I could search for any police complaints
against Miramax?

27:40.827 --> 27:42.412
Or court records?

27:44.414 --> 27:45.582
Should I?

27:46.750 --> 27:47.835
Yes.

27:48.585 --> 27:52.464
[Megan] I found records of a complaint
against Miramax from 2001,

27:52.548 --> 27:55.884
but the report was closed out
the same day it was made.

27:55.968 --> 27:58.637
It says, "complainant elected
court action,"

27:58.720 --> 28:02.057
but then no court documents exist,
which seems inconsistent.

28:02.140 --> 28:04.434
Do you have any more
information on that?

28:05.060 --> 28:07.688
[government official] No. Those records
would have been destroyed.

28:08.522 --> 28:10.065
Really? Why?

28:10.148 --> 28:11.733
It's agency policy.

28:11.817 --> 28:13.986
All records are destroyed
after three years.

28:14.945 --> 28:16.113
Why is that?

28:16.738 --> 28:19.658
As I said, it's policy.

28:20.951 --> 28:25.247
So could you please tell me
who filed the sexual harassment complaint?

28:25.330 --> 28:26.957
No, I cannot.

28:28.083 --> 28:30.836
-Because?
-It's policy.

28:30.919 --> 28:33.255
We are prohibited from
giving you that name.

28:34.089 --> 28:35.507
Is that everything?

28:36.592 --> 28:38.468
This is very important.

28:38.552 --> 28:41.930
It's about someone who's still
very powerful in the workplace.

28:42.014 --> 28:44.433
Who could still be harassing someone.

28:44.516 --> 28:46.727
Is there any way you can help me?

28:50.522 --> 28:52.983
You could ask me the name
of the government investigator

28:53.066 --> 28:54.818
who was assigned the case.

28:54.902 --> 28:56.862
I could give you that information.

28:57.696 --> 28:59.531
-Just a name.
-Thank you.

29:01.450 --> 29:04.494
I've made 20 calls
to track this investigator.

29:06.246 --> 29:07.998
What did Lisa Bloom say?

29:08.999 --> 29:12.961
She just talked as though
he was kind of naughty.

29:13.045 --> 29:15.214
She was talking to me
kind of Jew-to-Jew

29:15.297 --> 29:17.591
and including Weinstein
in the gang.

29:17.674 --> 29:18.884
Oh!

29:19.718 --> 29:24.056
I had a long conversation
with Lena Dunham and Jenni Konner.

29:24.139 --> 29:26.517
They wanna help,
and they have so many numbers.

29:26.600 --> 29:27.726
Amazing.

29:28.560 --> 29:29.937
Did you know them before?

29:30.020 --> 29:32.272
[chuckles]
I don't know anyone.

29:32.356 --> 29:34.441
-In April, when I started…
-[cell phone ringing]

29:34.525 --> 29:35.859
…I was literally leaving--

29:35.943 --> 29:37.277
It's the investigator.

29:38.278 --> 29:40.697
Hi, this is Megan Twohey.
Thank you for getting back to me.

29:40.781 --> 29:42.908
[investigator] Sure. How can I help?

29:42.991 --> 29:44.701
Do you remember the case?

29:44.785 --> 29:47.955
There are hundreds of
sexual harassment cases at that agency.

29:48.789 --> 29:52.751
This one was brought to you,
and then it was closed very quickly.

29:52.835 --> 29:54.461
That's not unusual.

29:55.420 --> 29:57.756
It was filed against Miramax?

29:58.715 --> 30:00.133
What's Miramax?

30:01.468 --> 30:02.469
[sighs]

30:04.638 --> 30:06.765
[Lisa] Harvey,
I've read the thorough reports,

30:06.849 --> 30:11.103
and Rose comes across as
a disturbed, pathological liar.

30:11.186 --> 30:15.232
Clearly she must be stopped in
her ridiculous, defamatory attacks on you.

30:15.983 --> 30:18.944
She is dangerous.
You are right to be concerned.

30:19.570 --> 30:23.031
I feel equipped to help you
against the Roses of the world,

30:23.115 --> 30:26.451
because I have represented
so many of them.

30:26.535 --> 30:29.121
I'd like to meet with you to go over this
in some detail.

30:29.204 --> 30:32.749
You should be the hero of this story,
not the villain.

30:32.833 --> 30:34.168
Best. Lisa Bloom.

30:36.295 --> 30:40.424
I'm trying to get ahold of this assistant
who worked at Miramax in her early 20s.

30:41.884 --> 30:43.969
One day, she just disappeared.

30:44.052 --> 30:46.847
All she left were her running shoes
under the table.

30:46.930 --> 30:50.225
I haven't been able to find her yet,
but her mother lives in Queens.

30:50.309 --> 30:51.810
I thought I'd just show up.

31:22.382 --> 31:23.759
[doorbell rings]

31:30.974 --> 31:32.809
-Hi.
-Hello.

31:33.602 --> 31:37.397
Hi. I was expecting your mother.

31:37.481 --> 31:38.982
Oh, I'll go get her.
Who should I say--

31:39.066 --> 31:40.692
No, it's-- it's actually--

31:40.776 --> 31:42.444
You're the one I wanted to see.

31:43.737 --> 31:44.947
Excuse me?

31:45.948 --> 31:47.491
My name is Megan Twohey.

31:47.574 --> 31:50.369
I am an investigative reporter
for The New York Times.

31:51.787 --> 31:53.247
Would it be okay if--

31:53.330 --> 31:55.499
Go back upstairs. Go see Abuelita.

32:04.132 --> 32:06.385
Could we talk for a minute…

32:07.970 --> 32:09.763
about your time at Miramax?

32:10.681 --> 32:11.807
[scoffs]

32:12.599 --> 32:14.560
I can't believe you found me.

32:16.144 --> 32:18.522
I've been waiting for this for 25 years.

32:21.191 --> 32:26.363
I would love the chance
to ask you a couple questions.

32:28.740 --> 32:30.242
What do you know?

32:31.660 --> 32:36.456
That you were at the beginning
of your career and doing well.

32:38.292 --> 32:40.377
And that something happened.

32:43.088 --> 32:44.840
And then you disappeared.

32:47.885 --> 32:50.220
And that your father
threatened legal action.

32:59.438 --> 33:00.480
[exhales]

33:03.734 --> 33:05.485
All I can tell you is that…

33:07.571 --> 33:11.867
I had a business dispute
with Miramax.

33:13.493 --> 33:14.912
It was resolved.

33:15.871 --> 33:17.122
Amicably.

33:18.415 --> 33:20.584
And we've agreed
not to discuss it.

33:24.129 --> 33:25.130
I'm…

33:26.048 --> 33:27.424
so glad to meet you anyway.

33:32.930 --> 33:34.014
So…

33:35.516 --> 33:37.267
it was "resolved"?

33:38.519 --> 33:41.063
Yeah. It was.

33:49.321 --> 33:52.115
There are women
who have had settlements,

33:53.158 --> 33:54.660
and they're bound to silence,

33:55.619 --> 33:58.121
but we have
written around them.

33:59.331 --> 34:01.875
There are ways to report around
that restriction.

34:01.959 --> 34:04.086
The source
can remain anonymous.

34:07.089 --> 34:08.382
[sniffles]

34:09.341 --> 34:11.134
I should go back in.

34:15.514 --> 34:16.639
Look, I'm--

34:17.474 --> 34:20.060
Sorry. I've thrown a curveball into
your trip to see your mother,

34:20.143 --> 34:21.895
and I don't wanna keep you
from your family,

34:21.978 --> 34:25.107
but would it be okay
if I gave you my number?

34:27.775 --> 34:32.322
She was terrified, Jodi,
but she wants to talk. She really does.

34:32.406 --> 34:34.408
[Jodi] Really? That's incredible.

34:35.074 --> 34:37.244
Listen, Gwyneth Paltrow called,

34:37.327 --> 34:40.496
and she told me about an incident
at The Peninsula hotel.

34:40.581 --> 34:42.291
The Peninsula?
What the fuck?

34:42.373 --> 34:44.501
Exactly. Where Ashley went to meet him.

34:44.585 --> 34:46.670
-Shit. What happened?
-[phone beeps]

34:47.713 --> 34:49.089
Fuck. It's her. I have to go.

34:49.630 --> 34:51.007
Hi.

34:51.091 --> 34:53.217
[former assistant] Megan, we just spoke.

34:53.302 --> 34:55.053
I'm sorry, but it's a no.

34:55.137 --> 34:56.889
But good luck. Honestly.

34:56.972 --> 34:58.223
[line clicks]

35:24.958 --> 35:28.086
[Talia] So if you sign it,
you don't tell anyone about anything?

35:28.170 --> 35:30.255
Yeah. It could've been bullying,

35:30.339 --> 35:32.799
or sometimes it's just a big shop,

35:32.883 --> 35:35.636
and they don't want you
to tell their trade secrets.

35:35.719 --> 35:37.054
Did you sign one?

35:37.137 --> 35:38.972
[chuckles] No.

35:39.515 --> 35:42.809
So, shops have secrets,
but newspapers don't?

35:47.606 --> 35:50.150
I think pretty much everyone
and everything has a secret.

35:50.234 --> 35:51.109
What's yours?

35:53.362 --> 35:56.156
I will tell you one day.
Do you have one?

35:56.740 --> 35:58.033
Of course.

36:01.578 --> 36:02.913
'Course I have a secret.

36:09.962 --> 36:11.547
[car door opens, closes]

36:14.174 --> 36:15.843
[chattering]

36:37.823 --> 36:39.324
[doorbell rings]

36:47.958 --> 36:49.793
-Hello?
-[Megan] John Schmidt?

36:49.877 --> 36:52.588
My name is Megan Twohey.
I'm a reporter from The New York Times.

36:52.671 --> 36:54.631
Would it be possible to speak
for a moment?

36:54.715 --> 36:55.966
Come in.

37:01.430 --> 37:03.015
I can't see what
you want from me.

37:03.682 --> 37:06.894
[Megan] You were
the chief financial officer at Miramax.

37:06.977 --> 37:10.272
The women who received these settlements,
they can't speak out.

37:10.355 --> 37:12.149
They'll be sued if they do.

37:13.192 --> 37:16.820
But if someone could speak freely
about the payouts,

37:17.696 --> 37:19.698
that would be hugely helpful.

37:22.743 --> 37:24.453
What payouts, John?

37:32.461 --> 37:34.087
I'm not asking you to go on the record.

37:34.171 --> 37:39.092
Just to have your perspective
on what might've happened back then.

37:45.974 --> 37:47.559
I need to think about it.

37:49.937 --> 37:50.938
Okay?

37:51.772 --> 37:52.773
Okay.

37:54.149 --> 37:55.692
Sorry just to show up.

38:00.072 --> 38:01.573
-Good night.
-[door opens]

38:01.657 --> 38:02.741
[John] Good night.

38:02.824 --> 38:04.117
[door closes]

38:11.458 --> 38:14.253
[breathing heavily]

38:20.884 --> 38:23.178
[Megan] Hi, hi. Can you hear me?

38:23.262 --> 38:24.388
[EEOC caller] Yes.

38:24.471 --> 38:27.391
[Megan] Uh, I really appreciate you
talking to me on a Saturday.

38:27.474 --> 38:29.518
[EEOC caller]
I hope the links were useful.

38:29.601 --> 38:32.145
They were,
but I find it very strange

38:32.229 --> 38:35.607
that if I wanna access
certain information, I can't.

38:35.691 --> 38:39.403
The EEOC is all about information.
What could you not find?

38:39.486 --> 38:43.073
Well, for instance, which companies have
had the most sexual harassment complaints,

38:43.156 --> 38:45.367
but no one was permitted to tell me that.

38:45.450 --> 38:47.870
Yes, that would be
confidential information.

38:48.453 --> 38:49.830
But do you think that's right?

38:49.913 --> 38:52.583
Shouldn't the Equal Employment
Opportunities Commission

38:52.666 --> 38:54.585
be a resource for information?

38:56.003 --> 38:58.005
Our policies are reviewed annually.

38:58.088 --> 39:01.842
So do you know internally
which companies have the most complaints?

39:01.925 --> 39:05.804
Yes. We do, but we're not allowed
to disclose that information.

39:07.055 --> 39:09.391
So any woman applying for a job

39:09.474 --> 39:15.063
is not allowed to check the record
of that employer in terms of harassment?

39:15.147 --> 39:18.942
That's right. You should probably
talk to someone higher up.

39:19.026 --> 39:21.028
[chuckles] I'm-- I'm going to.

39:21.111 --> 39:24.281
I will, but don't you think
that's strange?

39:24.364 --> 39:26.658
That the commission is there
to protect people,

39:26.742 --> 39:31.330
but its policy prohibits sharing
the information needed to protect them?

39:32.372 --> 39:36.627
Megan, I'm not the head of the EEOC.
