1:30:11.662 --> 1:30:12.704
Every day?

1:30:14.081 --> 1:30:15.624
I sometimes wonder…

1:30:18.794 --> 1:30:20.629
when I had Mira,

1:30:21.380 --> 1:30:22.381
if--

1:30:23.632 --> 1:30:24.842
if all the trauma,

1:30:24.925 --> 1:30:29.221
not just in me, but in all
of the women I talked to,

1:30:29.304 --> 1:30:30.305
if it just--

1:30:31.098 --> 1:30:35.686
This darkness, this constant violence,
if it just sort of imploded?

1:30:37.145 --> 1:30:41.400
Maybe that's part of the depression
that hits women.

1:30:45.362 --> 1:30:47.698
Do you wish you hadn't signed up
for this story?

1:30:50.200 --> 1:30:51.368
Do you?

1:30:53.537 --> 1:30:54.538
No.

1:30:55.372 --> 1:30:56.623
No. [chuckles]

1:31:04.131 --> 1:31:07.593
[Jodi] The last time we met,
you mentioned a memo?

1:31:15.100 --> 1:31:18.270
It was from an ex-executive.

1:31:18.353 --> 1:31:20.522
And it was extensive, scathing.

1:31:20.606 --> 1:31:22.191
She sent it to the board.

1:31:22.274 --> 1:31:24.651
When was this?
How did they react?

1:31:24.735 --> 1:31:27.946
It was a short burst
of behind-doors mayhem, and then she left.

1:31:29.156 --> 1:31:31.074
What did her memo say?

1:31:31.158 --> 1:31:33.243
That the company
was a toxic environment.

1:31:35.746 --> 1:31:37.206
Would anyone have a copy?

1:31:37.289 --> 1:31:38.999
[laughs]

1:31:44.213 --> 1:31:45.214
Hey.

1:31:47.174 --> 1:31:49.635
-Sorry it's so late.
-Mmm.

1:31:53.555 --> 1:31:54.556
[Jodi] You okay?

1:31:55.432 --> 1:31:58.310
Uh, Talia was up late.
Violet woke up twice.

1:31:58.393 --> 1:32:02.231
I have an inbox filled with enraged people
about this insurance story

1:32:02.314 --> 1:32:03.982
which is going to be huge.

1:32:04.066 --> 1:32:07.569
There's already hundreds of emails here,

1:32:07.653 --> 1:32:11.448
and there is… [chuckles]
…a hurricane heading towards Florida.

1:32:11.532 --> 1:32:13.575
So, I am going to somehow fly down there

1:32:13.659 --> 1:32:17.579
and move my dad someplace else
before he is literally blown away.

1:32:17.663 --> 1:32:20.624
And I have a slight nervous twitch
in my eye.

1:32:20.707 --> 1:32:21.792
Let me see.

1:32:25.128 --> 1:32:26.630
[sighs]

1:32:26.922 --> 1:32:28.382
Can you get the raisin?

1:32:28.465 --> 1:32:30.801
[both laughing]

1:32:30.884 --> 1:32:34.054
-Hey! Hey! Holly!
-[chattering, laughing]

1:32:35.097 --> 1:32:37.266
-[cell phone ringing]
-Slow down.

1:32:37.349 --> 1:32:39.101
Here.
Will you hold Crabby for a second?

1:32:39.184 --> 1:32:40.310
Least they're having fun.

1:32:41.645 --> 1:32:43.438
Hi. This is Jodi Kantor.

1:32:43.522 --> 1:32:46.149
This is Rowena Chiu.
I'm in New York.

1:32:46.942 --> 1:32:48.819
Do you still want to meet up?

1:32:50.028 --> 1:32:51.280
I couldn't tell anyone.

1:32:51.989 --> 1:32:54.491
Not my parents.
Not even my husband.

1:32:55.284 --> 1:32:56.285
Why not?

1:32:58.370 --> 1:33:00.706
I grew up in an immigrant household.

1:33:00.789 --> 1:33:03.333
I was taught to keep my head down,

1:33:03.417 --> 1:33:06.587
work hard and not draw attention
to myself, you know?

1:33:07.462 --> 1:33:11.967
In Chinese culture, I felt
I had to protect my family at all costs.

1:33:12.634 --> 1:33:15.679
And I was young, scared.

1:33:18.682 --> 1:33:21.351
Can you tell me anything
about what happened in Venice?

1:33:24.313 --> 1:33:26.899
This is off the record, yeah?

1:33:30.903 --> 1:33:32.404
I had the evening shifts,

1:33:32.487 --> 1:33:34.823
going through notes
on screenplays with Harvey.

1:33:35.699 --> 1:33:37.242
One night, we were working,

1:33:37.326 --> 1:33:40.787
and he kept trying to touch me.

1:33:41.538 --> 1:33:45.959
I didn't want to make him angry.
He's a very big man.

1:33:47.127 --> 1:33:49.379
I kept trying
to get back to the notes.

1:33:49.463 --> 1:33:54.510
And that went on for a few hours,
just trying to avoid him.

1:33:54.593 --> 1:33:56.220
How did you do that?

1:33:57.846 --> 1:34:00.557
I would just fight him off.

1:34:02.017 --> 1:34:06.271
I'd worn two pairs of tights
to buy me some time if I ever needed it.

1:34:07.856 --> 1:34:09.775
But finally,

1:34:10.692 --> 1:34:13.070
he held me down.

1:34:14.112 --> 1:34:17.157
Not forcefully,
but like it was a game.

1:34:19.284 --> 1:34:21.995
Then he parted my legs.

1:34:23.497 --> 1:34:24.748
And he said…

1:34:26.792 --> 1:34:30.629
"Please, just one thrust,
and it'll all be over."

1:34:34.967 --> 1:34:36.343
I got away.

1:34:36.426 --> 1:34:38.178
I was traumatized.

1:34:38.262 --> 1:34:41.181
I was a Christian.
I was still with my first boyfriend.

1:34:42.641 --> 1:34:45.185
And you shared this with Zelda?

1:34:45.269 --> 1:34:49.481
Zelda was completely enraged
and very brave in facing him.

1:34:50.315 --> 1:34:51.650
We both resigned.

1:34:54.027 --> 1:34:56.446
But I couldn't get a new job
after leaving Miramax.

1:34:57.155 --> 1:35:00.200
Everyone kept saying
if I worked for Harvey, why would I leave?

1:35:01.827 --> 1:35:04.538
The NDA that we signed,

1:35:04.621 --> 1:35:08.500
it stipulated that if I ever had trouble
getting a job in film again,

1:35:09.334 --> 1:35:12.838
I was to go back to Harvey
or his lawyer, Hutensky, for help.

1:35:14.089 --> 1:35:17.259
I asked them for a reference,

1:35:17.342 --> 1:35:21.763
and Hutensky, he kept repeating…

1:35:24.099 --> 1:35:25.726
What? What was he saying?

1:35:28.729 --> 1:35:30.981
How much Harvey valued me.

1:35:35.652 --> 1:35:38.655
We agreed I would return to Miramax

1:35:39.281 --> 1:35:41.033
under strict conditions.

1:35:43.452 --> 1:35:46.288
So, I signed for Hong Kong.

1:35:47.664 --> 1:35:50.334
I thought he would
be far enough away.

1:35:51.168 --> 1:35:52.544
I thought I'd be okay.

1:35:55.631 --> 1:35:57.216
But it was horrible.

1:35:58.592 --> 1:35:59.676
I was a mess.

1:36:00.385 --> 1:36:03.055
I felt incredibly alone.

1:36:04.348 --> 1:36:06.517
I couldn't tell anyone about it,

1:36:06.600 --> 1:36:10.020
and the isolation just ate into me.

1:36:11.522 --> 1:36:13.357
[speaking Cantonese]

1:36:18.654 --> 1:36:20.614
[Rowena] One day I disappeared from work.

1:36:23.033 --> 1:36:24.785
I wanted to be dead.

1:36:26.537 --> 1:36:28.080
I didn't know how to be,

1:36:28.789 --> 1:36:31.625
how to keep going, living with it.

1:36:33.961 --> 1:36:35.671
I tried to kill myself,

1:36:36.463 --> 1:36:39.174
but I didn't know how.

1:36:39.258 --> 1:36:40.592
[chuckles]

1:36:41.176 --> 1:36:43.136
I felt I failed at even that.

1:36:48.016 --> 1:36:49.351
I wanna give you this.

1:36:51.144 --> 1:36:55.190
It's a description from an actress
you would know and recognize.

1:37:10.622 --> 1:37:11.623
What?

1:37:11.707 --> 1:37:15.502
This person won't go on the record.
I can't put her in the story.

1:37:24.428 --> 1:37:25.804
[stammering] I-- I didn't--

1:37:26.555 --> 1:37:29.391
I didn't know anything like this.

1:37:33.228 --> 1:37:35.939
I thought it was just
extramarital bullshit.

1:37:36.690 --> 1:37:37.774
It's not.

1:38:04.718 --> 1:38:06.178
Do with it what you want.

1:38:32.204 --> 1:38:33.747
[camera shutter clicking]

1:38:58.564 --> 1:39:00.607
-[cell phone dings]
-[CNN reporter] …not a single bit

1:39:00.691 --> 1:39:02.401
of aid or assistance,

1:39:02.484 --> 1:39:04.736
and it's about 45 minutes' drive…

1:39:04.820 --> 1:39:05.821
Shit.

1:39:06.405 --> 1:39:07.406
This is it.

1:39:08.574 --> 1:39:09.700
This is it.

1:39:09.783 --> 1:39:11.535
[cell phone dings]

1:39:17.541 --> 1:39:21.170
[Lauren O'Connor] For your records.
November 3rd, 2015.

1:39:21.920 --> 1:39:26.425
I have experienced repeated harassment
and abuse from the head of this company.

1:39:27.259 --> 1:39:31.180
I am a 28-year-old woman
trying to make a living and a career.

1:39:31.847 --> 1:39:33.599
I am a professional.

1:39:33.682 --> 1:39:36.310
I am sexualized and diminished.

1:39:36.393 --> 1:39:38.687
I have been fearful about speaking up,

1:39:38.770 --> 1:39:42.357
but remaining silent
is causing me great distress.

1:39:42.441 --> 1:39:44.276
He told me, "I'm a bad boy,

1:39:44.359 --> 1:39:47.029
but what's important
is that I'm honest about it."

1:39:47.112 --> 1:39:50.782
He said the only thing
I was good for was making babies.

1:39:50.866 --> 1:39:55.537
An assistant told me Harvey made her
give him a massage while he was naked.

1:39:55.621 --> 1:39:58.916
It was horrible to see her so upset.

1:39:58.999 --> 1:40:02.586
When I complained
to their human resources executive,

1:40:02.669 --> 1:40:08.300
the response was, "Let us know if
he hits you or crosses a line physically."

1:40:08.383 --> 1:40:12.971
Harvey Weinstein is
a 64-year-old world-famous man,

1:40:13.055 --> 1:40:15.349
and this is his company.

1:40:15.432 --> 1:40:20.521
The balance of power is me, zero,
Harvey Weinstein, ten.

1:40:30.739 --> 1:40:31.865
Go write.

1:40:31.949 --> 1:40:33.075
[Matt] You've got the story.

1:40:33.158 --> 1:40:34.785
Once we publish,
everything else will come out.

1:40:34.868 --> 1:40:37.037
-And talk to Lauren O'Connor.
-Yeah.

1:40:37.120 --> 1:40:39.540
Get ahold of the Weinstein Company board
for their response.

1:40:39.623 --> 1:40:41.583
Let me call Lance Maerov.

1:40:41.667 --> 1:40:43.085
Write it. Let's get ready.

1:40:46.755 --> 1:40:49.007
[lawyer]
My client does not want to be named.

1:40:49.091 --> 1:40:51.677
That memo was never
for public distribution.

1:40:51.760 --> 1:40:52.761
[Rebecca] Lauren.

1:40:53.470 --> 1:40:56.598
[lawyer] My client is here,
but she's too upset to speak.

1:40:56.682 --> 1:40:59.434
Lauren, I'm sorry
this is difficult for you.

1:40:59.518 --> 1:41:01.687
We're not gonna publish the whole memo.

1:41:01.770 --> 1:41:04.898
And we will make it absolutely clear
you were not the source

1:41:04.982 --> 1:41:06.608
and that you declined to comment.

1:41:07.359 --> 1:41:10.571
But we do intend to use your name
for its credibility.

1:41:11.196 --> 1:41:15.117
If you were a victim of sexual assault,
we would absolutely keep your anonymity.

1:41:15.826 --> 1:41:17.661
But as a witness to what went on,

1:41:17.744 --> 1:41:21.123
it would make this story much stronger
to name you.

1:41:21.206 --> 1:41:24.084
Hi, Lance. This is Megan Twohey
from The New York Times.

1:41:24.168 --> 1:41:27.379
We have a memo here from Lauren O'Connor
to The Weinstein Company.

1:41:27.462 --> 1:41:28.881
What? Shit.

1:41:28.964 --> 1:41:30.424
We wanna know,
what did you do about it?

1:41:30.507 --> 1:41:32.259
What did the board do about it?

1:41:37.723 --> 1:41:38.724
Lance?

1:41:39.725 --> 1:41:43.187
We did try to change things
with the police complaint in 2015.

1:41:43.270 --> 1:41:46.023
What about this memo?
It was there and then it was gone?

1:41:46.106 --> 1:41:49.526
Look, we were all worried
about Harvey's behavior.

1:41:49.610 --> 1:41:51.445
Can I quote you, Lance?

1:41:54.489 --> 1:41:55.490
Yes.

1:41:56.116 --> 1:41:57.743
Yes, you can.

1:41:58.452 --> 1:42:00.120
So, Lauren's complaint?

1:42:03.373 --> 1:42:06.752
It was withdrawn days after it was sent.

1:42:06.835 --> 1:42:08.045
So, yeah, I let it go.

1:42:08.128 --> 1:42:10.088
Well, why do you think it was withdrawn?

1:42:10.881 --> 1:42:12.341
I really don't know why.

1:42:13.592 --> 1:42:16.553
Look, are you sure
that this isn't just young women

1:42:16.637 --> 1:42:19.431
who wanna sleep with a movie producer
to try to get ahead?

1:42:20.682 --> 1:42:22.851
We have decades of allegations,

1:42:23.435 --> 1:42:26.772
accusations of harassment,
assault, rape,

1:42:26.855 --> 1:42:28.607
and multiple settlements.

1:42:31.485 --> 1:42:33.320
I know you're gonna need to
speak to the board,

1:42:33.403 --> 1:42:35.197
but could you wait
until after the weekend?

1:42:36.823 --> 1:42:37.908
Is that possible?

1:42:38.534 --> 1:42:39.743
[clears throat]

1:42:40.827 --> 1:42:41.828
Okay.

1:42:51.129 --> 1:42:52.130
[Jodi] Ashley,

1:42:52.798 --> 1:42:55.592
I know that ideally a lot of women
would be jumping together,

1:42:55.676 --> 1:42:57.135
but that's not what's happening.

1:42:58.554 --> 1:43:02.516
But we do have a series of incidents
and a predatory pattern.

1:43:03.141 --> 1:43:05.018
You would be coming forward alone,

1:43:05.102 --> 1:43:07.938
but you would be standing
on a mountain of evidence.

1:43:11.650 --> 1:43:12.693
Ashley?

1:43:13.360 --> 1:43:16.530
Yes. I'll think about it
very seriously, Jodi.

1:43:17.197 --> 1:43:18.532
I promise.

1:43:18.615 --> 1:43:19.867
Thank you, Ashley.

1:43:20.492 --> 1:43:21.660
[line clicks]

1:43:24.204 --> 1:43:25.747
[Dean] We go with what we have.

1:43:25.831 --> 1:43:28.375
I know we need to be mindful
of The New Yorker,

1:43:28.458 --> 1:43:31.962
but couldn't we wait just a little longer,
just for these women to commit?

1:43:32.045 --> 1:43:33.714
No. We need to publish.

1:43:33.797 --> 1:43:35.632
It's nothing like the whole story.

1:43:35.716 --> 1:43:38.844
This can be the first arrow.
More women will come forward afterwards.

1:43:39.595 --> 1:43:41.763
It could be
so much stronger, Dean.

1:43:42.347 --> 1:43:43.348
It's solid.

1:43:44.141 --> 1:43:45.267
We need to go.

1:43:45.851 --> 1:43:49.354
How much time will we give Weinstein
to respond?

1:43:49.438 --> 1:43:50.480
Twenty-four hours?

1:43:50.564 --> 1:43:51.607
[Rebecca] I'd double it.

1:43:52.191 --> 1:43:54.026
Forty-eight hours. That's fair.

1:43:54.109 --> 1:43:55.110
[Dean] Two days?

1:43:55.194 --> 1:43:57.404
How many people could
Harvey and his team talk to

1:43:57.487 --> 1:43:58.655
in that amount of time?

1:44:00.324 --> 1:44:01.325
David?

1:44:02.242 --> 1:44:03.702
I'd go with Rebecca.

1:44:03.785 --> 1:44:06.163
We want to be irreproachable
from the legal side.

1:44:06.246 --> 1:44:07.831
[Dean] Good. Let's call Lanny.

1:44:07.915 --> 1:44:10.626
We'll ask to speak to Harvey
and his team at one o'clock tomorrow.

1:44:10.709 --> 1:44:11.877
We'll tell them what we have

1:44:12.461 --> 1:44:16.340
and give him, uh,
two days to respond or refute.

1:44:26.892 --> 1:44:29.186
It's midnight. Go home.

1:44:29.269 --> 1:44:30.646
-We will.
-Good night.

1:44:30.729 --> 1:44:32.564
[typing]

1:44:49.873 --> 1:44:52.626
If just one of the women
would have gone on the record…

1:44:53.126 --> 1:44:54.753
Why is he taking the tunnel?

1:44:56.255 --> 1:44:58.715
We just needed one woman.

1:44:58.799 --> 1:45:00.509
Jodi. Stop it.

1:45:01.176 --> 1:45:02.177
Let it go.

1:45:09.059 --> 1:45:11.979
Maybe if we had been able to
get them all into a room together.

1:45:13.689 --> 1:45:15.524
A room would make no difference.

1:45:16.859 --> 1:45:19.319
They don't wanna go on the record
by themselves.

1:45:21.530 --> 1:45:23.073
Would you want to?

1:45:33.375 --> 1:45:35.460
[sighs]

1:45:41.925 --> 1:45:42.926
[whispers] Hi.

1:45:45.804 --> 1:45:46.889
Yeah.

1:45:47.681 --> 1:45:48.682
Hi.

1:45:49.183 --> 1:45:50.184
Hi.

1:45:50.267 --> 1:45:52.936
Shh, shh, shh, shh…

1:45:53.020 --> 1:45:55.689
-[cooing]
-Shh, shh, shh, shh…

1:46:02.529 --> 1:46:04.448
It's been two fucking hours.

1:46:05.949 --> 1:46:06.950
It's a tactic,

1:46:07.576 --> 1:46:10.037
but I have things to do.

1:46:14.875 --> 1:46:16.668
[phone ringing]

1:46:22.341 --> 1:46:23.342
Hello?

1:46:23.425 --> 1:46:27.638
[secretary] Dean? I have Harvey Weinstein
and his lawyer, Charles Harder, for you.

1:46:28.430 --> 1:46:29.723
Okay, let's go, team.

1:46:31.099 --> 1:46:32.893
-You ready?
-We're ready.

1:46:34.478 --> 1:46:35.521
Put them through.

1:46:39.733 --> 1:46:41.151
Harvey?

1:46:41.235 --> 1:46:42.528
Charles?

1:46:42.611 --> 1:46:43.612
[Charles] Dean.

1:46:44.488 --> 1:46:46.114
How do you wanna do this,
Harvey?

1:46:46.782 --> 1:46:48.659
[Harvey] I don't wanna do this,
is what I want.

1:46:48.742 --> 1:46:51.161
Are they there?
The reporters?

1:46:51.245 --> 1:46:52.538
We're all here.

1:46:53.121 --> 1:46:54.498
[Harvey] Who have you talked to?

1:46:55.832 --> 1:46:58.544
We've sent you
who we're covering, Harvey.

1:46:58.627 --> 1:47:00.295
Who have you talked to?

1:47:00.379 --> 1:47:02.297
[chattering]

1:47:04.758 --> 1:47:05.843
[Megan] Harvey, we need some--

1:47:05.926 --> 1:47:07.469
[Harvey]
Are you talking to Gwyneth Paltrow?

1:47:07.553 --> 1:47:10.222
[Dean] Gwyneth's not in the story, Harvey.

1:47:10.305 --> 1:47:14.142
Why don't you tell me who's on the record
and let me respond to that?

1:47:14.226 --> 1:47:15.227
Yeah.

1:47:16.854 --> 1:47:20.691
Harvey, how many settlements
have you paid out over the years?

1:47:21.567 --> 1:47:23.610
We were told eight to 12.

1:47:23.694 --> 1:47:26.321
That's you talking. That's not me talking.

1:47:26.405 --> 1:47:30.325
If Lanny spoke, he spoke for himself
and not on behalf of his client.

1:47:34.788 --> 1:47:37.332
[Charles] How much time
are you giving us to respond?

1:47:37.416 --> 1:47:38.834
We need two weeks.

1:47:40.460 --> 1:47:42.004
You'll have two days.

1:47:42.087 --> 1:47:43.755
[Charles] This goes back to the '90s.

1:47:43.839 --> 1:47:46.175
[Harvey] If you mess up
and don't tell the truth,

1:47:46.258 --> 1:47:48.135
how do you look yourself in the eye?

1:47:48.218 --> 1:47:50.762
It's been 90 minutes, Harvey,
and we're gonna wrap it up now.

1:48:03.317 --> 1:48:05.569
[breathing heavily]

1:48:20.334 --> 1:48:22.836
[Dean] Harvey's just disputed
Lanny's eight to 12.

1:48:22.920 --> 1:48:24.171
We have to have corroboration.

1:48:24.254 --> 1:48:26.423
Eight to 12 settlements
has to be backed up.

1:48:27.382 --> 1:48:29.176
-Who can you call at the company?
-[cell phone ringing]

1:48:29.259 --> 1:48:30.886
I'll ask David Glasser.

1:48:30.969 --> 1:48:32.179
It's Ashley.

1:48:34.556 --> 1:48:36.266
Pick up. Answer it.

1:48:36.350 --> 1:48:37.392
I am. I am.

1:48:40.229 --> 1:48:41.271
Ashley.

1:48:42.648 --> 1:48:44.024
How are you?

1:48:44.107 --> 1:48:46.527
I'm good. Yeah. I'm good.
I just went for a run.

1:48:47.319 --> 1:48:49.947
[Jodi] That's great. That's great.
Running is good.

1:48:51.448 --> 1:48:52.658
I talked to my lawyer,

1:48:52.741 --> 1:48:55.619
and I've been thinking
about what the right thing to do is.

1:48:55.702 --> 1:48:57.204
Yeah. Of course.

1:48:57.788 --> 1:48:58.789
Of course.

1:49:02.000 --> 1:49:03.001
And?

1:49:05.963 --> 1:49:08.757
I'm prepared to be a named source
in your investigation.

1:49:10.217 --> 1:49:11.468
I have to…

1:49:12.553 --> 1:49:14.054
as a woman and a Christian.

1:49:20.185 --> 1:49:21.186
[exhales]

1:49:22.187 --> 1:49:23.188
[Ashley] Jodi?

1:49:24.231 --> 1:49:25.232
Yes.

1:49:26.024 --> 1:49:27.150
We'll speak soon.

1:49:29.194 --> 1:49:30.320
Yes.

1:49:30.404 --> 1:49:31.822
Ashley, thank you.

1:49:32.406 --> 1:49:33.490
Thank you.

1:49:35.826 --> 1:49:37.703
Ashley said yes. [crying]

1:49:38.287 --> 1:49:39.580
She said yes.

1:49:42.124 --> 1:49:43.125
Ashley said yes.

1:49:43.208 --> 1:49:45.919
She did, Jodi. She did. [laughs]

1:49:46.003 --> 1:49:49.381
Okay. Here we go
with the whole damn story.

1:49:49.464 --> 1:49:52.176
[Rebecca] The lede is Ashley Judd's
account of the Peninsula suite.

1:49:52.259 --> 1:49:54.261
Get a good Judd quote
to end the section.

1:49:54.344 --> 1:49:55.345
I'm on it.

1:49:55.429 --> 1:49:57.639
[Dean] We publish as soon as
the piece is in good shape.

1:49:57.723 --> 1:49:59.141
Let's go.

1:50:33.133 --> 1:50:34.760
[line ringing]

1:50:37.095 --> 1:50:38.472
-Hello?
-Hi, David.

1:50:38.555 --> 1:50:41.141
This is Megan Twohey
from The New York Times.

1:50:41.225 --> 1:50:44.228
I thought it was fair to give you,
as company president, a chance to comment.

1:50:44.311 --> 1:50:45.687
Are you up to speed with everything?

1:50:47.272 --> 1:50:48.440
I am.

1:50:48.524 --> 1:50:51.026
The board had
an emergency conference call.

1:50:51.735 --> 1:50:54.821
David, the eight to 12 settlements,
we have conflicting reports.

1:50:54.905 --> 1:50:55.948
We don't need to name you,

1:50:56.031 --> 1:50:58.825
but would you confirm for me
that eight to 12 is accurate?

1:50:58.909 --> 1:51:00.035
How many?

1:51:00.619 --> 1:51:03.372
Eight to 12.
Are we safe using that figure?

1:51:06.166 --> 1:51:07.543
Eight to 12.

1:51:10.796 --> 1:51:12.840
Uh, yeah. Yes. That's accurate.

1:51:13.423 --> 1:51:15.300
I appreciate it, David. Thank you.

1:51:16.426 --> 1:51:17.886
[elevator bell dings]

1:51:23.058 --> 1:51:24.393
[sighs]

1:51:38.282 --> 1:51:40.993
David Glasser says yes
to eight to 12 settlements.

1:51:43.370 --> 1:51:45.163
[both laughing]

1:51:45.247 --> 1:51:46.331
[Lanny] It's not enough time.

1:51:46.415 --> 1:51:47.791
-It's not just me here.
-[Megan] Right. Yeah.

1:51:47.875 --> 1:51:49.459
-You must know that, right?
-[Megan] Yep.

1:51:49.543 --> 1:51:51.003
I understand it's difficult.

1:51:51.962 --> 1:51:53.589
What's happening?
Is Harvey on the phone?

1:51:53.672 --> 1:51:56.341
It's Lanny. Weinstein is refusing
to give a response.

1:51:56.425 --> 1:51:57.759
-[Megan] Okay.
-[Lanny] Right?

1:51:57.843 --> 1:52:00.095
[Megan] Yeah.
No, Lanny, I hear you.

1:52:00.179 --> 1:52:02.931
Listen, I can't pull a rabbit
out of a hat here.

1:52:03.015 --> 1:52:04.516
We need more time.

1:52:04.600 --> 1:52:05.601
Here's the thing, Megan--

1:52:05.684 --> 1:52:06.852
Lanny, I'm sick of this shit.

1:52:06.935 --> 1:52:08.979
You've got five different lawyers
reaching out to us.

1:52:09.062 --> 1:52:11.064
We're not talking
to five different lawyers.

1:52:11.148 --> 1:52:14.610
Get your people in line
and get back to us with your response.

1:52:21.825 --> 1:52:23.702
This is not a response. This is a novel.

1:52:23.785 --> 1:52:26.663
They call the women liars
and the journalism false.

1:52:26.747 --> 1:52:28.707
It's legalistic bullying.

1:52:28.790 --> 1:52:31.376
I sent back three paragraphs
to counter their 18 pages.

1:52:31.460 --> 1:52:32.836
I've asked for their data.

1:52:32.920 --> 1:52:35.547
-And I invite them to court.
-Let's see how long

1:52:35.631 --> 1:52:37.674
-before they get back to us.
-[cell phone buzzes]

1:52:39.510 --> 1:52:40.677
Waiting time's up.

1:52:40.761 --> 1:52:42.804
Weinstein wants to meet.
He's on his way here.

1:52:43.388 --> 1:52:44.389
Do we let him in?

1:52:47.684 --> 1:52:48.685
Let him in.

1:52:49.478 --> 1:52:50.479
I've got this.

1:53:01.198 --> 1:53:02.449
-Hi, Lisa.
-Hi.

1:53:02.533 --> 1:53:03.992
-Is this everyone?
-Yep.

1:53:04.076 --> 1:53:05.369
[Megan] Okay, follow me.

1:53:09.790 --> 1:53:12.084
-That's what you're gonna do.
-Only five. Come on. We've got folders.

1:53:12.167 --> 1:53:13.752
We have the folders.
We've got evidence.

1:53:13.836 --> 1:53:15.587
You're a good writer, Megan.

1:53:15.671 --> 1:53:18.674
[Harvey] Are you really willing to stake
your reputation on this story?

1:53:18.757 --> 1:53:22.052
-She's smiling. Everybody looks happy.
-Would you smile if this happened to you?

1:53:22.135 --> 1:53:24.721
None of these women
are credible witnesses.

1:53:24.805 --> 1:53:26.056
How's this one?

1:53:26.139 --> 1:53:27.724
[Harvey] She's a nut.

1:53:27.808 --> 1:53:29.434
She's a shakedown artist.

1:53:29.518 --> 1:53:31.270
[chattering]

1:53:59.840 --> 1:54:01.383
[Jodi] Is it there? Is it online?

1:54:01.466 --> 1:54:03.468
Yes. They have it too.

1:54:03.552 --> 1:54:04.595
So it's in both.

1:54:06.847 --> 1:54:07.848
What happened?

1:54:08.974 --> 1:54:10.601
What you'd expect.

1:54:10.684 --> 1:54:12.603
Trying to discredit the actresses.

1:54:12.686 --> 1:54:13.687
What's wrong?

1:54:14.688 --> 1:54:17.941
Harvey and his team have spoken to
Variety and Hollywood Reporter.

1:54:18.567 --> 1:54:20.652
-What?
-About us and the story.

1:54:20.736 --> 1:54:23.614
He claims to be surprised by it.

1:54:24.364 --> 1:54:25.741
This is bad.

1:54:27.034 --> 1:54:30.120
You have to write fast.
We've just lost any privacy.

1:54:31.747 --> 1:54:33.373
Let me see the lede.

1:54:33.457 --> 1:54:34.791
[typing]

1:54:41.256 --> 1:54:43.842
[Jodi] All I think is
we have to lead with this.

1:54:43.926 --> 1:54:45.719
That has to be
at the top of the paragraph.

1:54:45.802 --> 1:54:48.138
-I think it's fine as two, don't you?
-[Rebecca] I think it's right.

1:54:50.265 --> 1:54:52.893
Go home. I'll check this.

1:54:55.103 --> 1:54:56.104
Really?

1:55:15.207 --> 1:55:16.959
[news anchor]
And they're really appealing to people.

1:55:17.042 --> 1:55:19.378
If you know anything,
please come forward.

1:55:33.141 --> 1:55:35.269
[Harvey] Why shouldn't I just do
a fucking interview right now

1:55:35.352 --> 1:55:38.522
with The Washington Post
based on your lack of transparency?

1:55:38.605 --> 1:55:41.483
You want some sort of list of
who we're talking to for this story,

1:55:41.567 --> 1:55:44.653
and if we don't disclose it to you,
you're threatening us?

1:55:44.736 --> 1:55:46.989
If you're using Gwyneth Paltrow, tell me.

1:55:47.072 --> 1:55:49.032
We're not using Gwyneth Paltrow.

1:55:49.116 --> 1:55:51.201
Are you talking to Gwyneth Paltrow?

1:55:52.911 --> 1:55:54.913
Hey, Harvey. This is Dean.
Here's the deal.

1:55:54.997 --> 1:55:58.000
You need to give us your statement now.
I'm about to push the button.

1:55:58.083 --> 1:56:00.502
Dean, let me tell you something
about intimidation.

1:56:00.586 --> 1:56:02.045
I'll talk to The Post. I will.

1:56:02.129 --> 1:56:03.672
Call them. That's fine.

1:56:03.755 --> 1:56:05.382
You can call The Post.

1:56:05.465 --> 1:56:07.301
Harvey, I'm trying to be fair with you.

1:56:07.384 --> 1:56:08.844
You are intimidating me, Dean.

1:56:08.927 --> 1:56:11.680
No, I'm trying to get your statement.
Please, give it to us now.

1:56:11.763 --> 1:56:13.765
We're about to publish.

1:56:13.849 --> 1:56:16.101
-I want to give it to you.
-Thank you.

1:56:16.185 --> 1:56:17.519
Is Gwyneth in it?

1:56:17.603 --> 1:56:19.104
[both] She's not in the story.

1:56:19.188 --> 1:56:21.440
So here's what
we need to do, Harvey.

1:56:22.274 --> 1:56:24.860
We wanna give you every word
that you wanna say.

1:56:25.652 --> 1:56:26.778
So say it.

1:56:27.446 --> 1:56:30.199
I also have a newspaper to put out.
I'm gonna walk out.

1:56:30.282 --> 1:56:32.284
Talk to my reporters.
Take care.

1:56:33.368 --> 1:56:34.411
Good luck.

1:56:34.494 --> 1:56:37.372
[Lisa] You have a reckless disregard
for the truth.

1:56:37.456 --> 1:56:41.084
You want a hit story,
and these allegations are false.

1:56:41.168 --> 1:56:43.462
We don't want
a hit story, Lisa.

1:56:43.545 --> 1:56:46.757
Harvey's going to take some time off
to focus on this issue.

1:56:48.383 --> 1:56:49.551
Are you, Harvey?

1:56:50.344 --> 1:56:52.679
[Harvey] Yes, I'm gonna take time off.

1:56:53.388 --> 1:56:54.890
From the company?

1:56:55.557 --> 1:56:58.560
Yes. I wanna spend some time learning.

1:56:58.644 --> 1:57:01.647
-[Lisa] Learning and listening to me.
-He's going to take a leave of absence.

1:57:02.523 --> 1:57:04.107
Double space here.

1:57:04.983 --> 1:57:06.985
-And here.
-[cell phone buzzing]

1:57:07.569 --> 1:57:08.654
It's Laura.

1:57:11.406 --> 1:57:13.450
Hi. Laura, how are you?

1:57:14.201 --> 1:57:17.287
Yes, I'm okay.

1:57:17.371 --> 1:57:18.455
Today's my surgery.

1:57:19.081 --> 1:57:20.707
I'm about to go in.

1:57:20.791 --> 1:57:25.045
Um, look, I never signed any contract.

1:57:25.838 --> 1:57:27.381
I'm not gagged,

1:57:28.090 --> 1:57:31.552
and I want to speak out
on behalf of the women who can't.

1:57:33.512 --> 1:57:34.721
I have three daughters,

1:57:34.805 --> 1:57:38.600
and I don't want them to
ever accept abuse or bullying as normal.

1:57:40.060 --> 1:57:42.563
You can use anything I've said.

1:57:43.230 --> 1:57:44.439
I'll do it.

1:57:45.607 --> 1:57:47.568
I'll go on the record.

1:57:49.862 --> 1:57:50.988
Thank you, Laura.

1:57:52.364 --> 1:57:53.365
Thank you.

1:57:55.075 --> 1:57:56.702
I'll be thinking of you.

1:58:01.540 --> 1:58:02.875
[sighs]

1:58:07.129 --> 1:58:08.922
-Oh, Laura.
-[laughs]

1:58:09.006 --> 1:58:11.049
Oh, beautiful,
beautiful Laura.

1:58:24.438 --> 1:58:25.898
[nurse]
Are you okay, Laura?

1:58:25.981 --> 1:58:28.483
[laughs] Yes. I'm fine.

1:58:28.567 --> 1:58:29.568
Thank you.

1:58:31.320 --> 1:58:32.696
I really am.

1:59:00.766 --> 1:59:02.267
[chattering]

1:59:49.606 --> 1:59:51.859
Their statements are in.
I'm pulling quotes.

1:59:53.569 --> 1:59:54.570
Yep.

1:59:59.283 --> 2:00:01.493
So, do you-- Okay. You're so good.
[laughs]

2:00:20.846 --> 2:00:23.098
-Have you pulled the quotes?
-I'm doing it now.

2:00:39.323 --> 2:00:40.741
It's ready to go.

2:00:40.824 --> 2:00:43.952
Let's read it together one last time.

2:01:18.487 --> 2:01:19.488
Yeah.

2:01:20.030 --> 2:01:21.073
One second.

2:01:25.160 --> 2:01:26.286
Yeah.

2:01:27.412 --> 2:01:28.413
Okay?

2:01:30.415 --> 2:01:31.416
[Dean] Okay?

2:01:34.169 --> 2:01:35.170
-Yeah.
-Okay.

